A Republican Strategy to confront Obama ’ s Reselection
Republicans are justifying their policy with the need to combat electoral fraud .
However , the Brennan Center is a myth of a myth that the electoral fraud in the US is less than the number of people killed by the lightning .
The Republicans ’ lawyers in 10 years in the US , incidentally , recorded only 300 cases of electoral fraud .
One thing is certain : these new rules will have a negative impact on voter participation
In this sense , these measures undermine the democratic system of the United States
Unlike Canada , the US States are responsible for holding elections in the various states .
In this sense , the majority of American governments have proclaimed new legislation since 2009 , which makes the procedure for registration or the call for a crime more difficult
This phenomenon has become important after the elections of November 2010 , which 675 new Republican representatives in 26 countries could be recorded .
As a result , 180 draft draft laws were introduced alone in 2011 , which limits the exercise of electoral rights in 41 States .
The new electoral laws require that the electorate be presented with a light card and proof of US citizenship .
Moreover , these laws also shorten the time for the temporary vote , the right to be rescited to the electorate , and to the right to vote , for which a court is present .
Before the 2006 elections , no US state required a US state to show a light card .
Indiana was the first state to demand such a claim .
The Supreme Court of the United States confirmed the constitution of Indiana in 2008 .
The Republican authorities were eager to extend this practice to other countries .
Over the past two years , they have encouraged in 34 states draft laws to force voters to show a light card .
It is important to note that , unlike Quebec , US citizens do not have a universal card card such as health insurance cards .
In fact , 11 % of US citizens , that is to say 21 million , are not eligible for the light card issued by a government authority .
Moreover , five million new voters in 2012 do not have such a passport .
However , there are often more than a hundred dollars to pay to receive the necessary ID .
The new restrictions are disproportionate to young people , minorities and low-income people .
In fact , 25 % of African-Americans , 15 % of people with a income of less than $ 35,000 , 18 % of citizens over 65 years , and 20 % of the electorate between 18 and 29 years do not have the
That is still sufficient .
The students , who are seen as voters , who are more qualified for democratic candidates , are not allowed to use their own light card to use their own institution .
On the other hand , the same countries allow members of fishing or hunting to choose more for the Republican side to use the cards issued by these clubs .
2004 , no federal state asked for a state citizenship certificate .
Arizona was the first state to introduce such a demand .
Since 2011 , a dozen countries have passed legislation demanding that they prove their American citizenship .
These measures are aimed clearly at limiting Hizpanic voices .
It is obvious that two of three Hizpanic voters who prefer democratic party are the two .
Moreover , in eight federal states in 2011 , Republican legislators promoted legislation to abolish the registration of voters on the day of voting .
You also have limited the right of individuals and groups to help those constituents who wish to register .
These restrictions are not without consequences .
For example , the electoral register for the 2004 general elections has contributed to a further 10 million citizens .
The measures adopted since 2009 have reduced the share of registration of new voters by 17 % compared to 2006 .
Moreover , Republican legislators in five other federal states have adopted legislation aimed at shortening the period for the pre-election vote .
For example , in the 2008 general election in Florida , 33 % of voters who elected in advance were African-Americans , although they only account for 13 % of the federal state
The same applies to the Hizpanan population .
The latter only made 11 % of the electorate , but 24 % of the citizens elected in advance .
By contrast , the wholly-out of 76 % of voters made only 46 % of voters who chose in advance .
Of course , democratic legislators and their supporters have consistently opposed the adoption of laws that restrict the registration of voters .
Several draft laws have been blocked by the powers of the democratic governor .
The United States General Advisor has intervened to suspend the most controversial laws .
They could partially limit the damage .
For example , only 16 of the 34 states have adopted legislation that requires a light card indication .
However , the new rules introduced in 2012 will undoubtedly make the exercise of electoral law more difficult .
Democratic critics denounce the party political nature of the laws adopted and they see it as a clear goal to influence the results in the countries that are to be held in 2012 .
A report by the Brennan Center in 2011 shows that those States that adopted these laws , 171 of the 270 votes required to win the Presidency , are required to win .
It is too soon to confirm with certainty that these changes to the electoral system legislation will have a major impact on the outcome of the presidential elections in 2012 .
But one thing is certain : these new rules will have a negative impact on voter participation
In this sense , these measures undermine the democratic system of the United States
Prostate cancer diagnosis : should the test be carried out or not ?
The PSA-Test , in fact , sometimes produces flawed results , with false or incorrect results , which lead to unnecessary medical interventions .
This leads to greater reluctance by the already indecisive men to carry out screening tests .
Should the test be done or not ?
We have taken up the opinion of two medical doctors .
The studies carried out in the USA have had a number of disturbances between the control groups , so it is difficult to interpret this data and give clear recommendations .
Another study , this time from Europe , concluded that there is a difference in the mortality of patients with and without early diagnosis .
This study also showed that after 12 years the probability of formation of metastases by 30 to 40 % is a 30 % higher if no screening is carried out .
I recommend , therefore , that the test should be carried out from 50 years or 40 years , when one has a direct relatives who have already been infected with prostate cancer .
There is also a higher risk in men of afro-American origin
The most important thing is to take the right decision once a cancer disease has been identified .
There are cancers that are aggressive and others that are indolent .
Patients must be made to understand the extent of the risk of cancer , by indicating the possible options for which prostate cancer can be treated , if it does not harm quality of life in the long run , and in these cases , it is more likely to be able to take an active role in the disease .
Today , many men in cancer , in which cancer is recognized , do not treat them because their cancer is not aggressive and does not pose a threat to their lives
They are proposing active monitoring and are offering treatment to them when the disease continues .
It is determined to be the criteria for deciding who should be treated and who does not .
I therefore recommend that the tests be carried out
But most importantly , it is up to your doctor to decide to determine whether or not to be carried out .
In cooperation with the international company for Urology , Movember developed an instrument to assess the advantages and disadvantages of PAT tests .
