Prevention of the disease
Unfortunately , there is no miracle cure for cancer .
Despite progress in research , the adoption of a healthy way of life remains the best way to reduce the risk to him .
It is estimated that 30 % of cancers could be prevented if all the patients are eating and doing enough .
&quot; If there were no smoking , this value would rise at least to 50 % &quot; , André Beaulieu , spokesperson of Canadian cancer society .
However , it is assumed that about 10 % of cancers are caused by inheritance .
Several remain unexplained .
The fight against tobacco addiction remains a priority for the Canadian Cancer Society , despite the decline in the number of smokers .
Smoking is responsible for 85 % of lung cancer .
It is also a risk factor for several other types of cancer .
It damages people &apos;s health seriously .
&quot; Today there are 1.5 million smokers in Quebec , &quot; he regrets André Beaulieu .
Tightening data : 10 years after the withdrawal of cigarette , the risk of cancer is reduced by half .
The weight
According to Canadian cancer society , over-weight and obesity also promote outbreak of disease .
They seem to increase the risk of breast , flu , mastom , muffle , and pancreatic cancer and cervical cancer .
&quot; Research shows that regular physical activity is protected during the whole life against flu cancer , &quot; adds to it .
Food
The organization also recommends limiting the consumption of red meat .
Too much increases in the risk of becoming a grim or mastommicide .
It should be avoided .
The conservation of meat by smoked , dry or salt can lead to the formation of carcinogens .
&quot; The latter can damage body cells and lead to the development of cancer &quot; , explains it .
Vitamins
In recent years several scientists have examined the connection between vitamins and cancer .
However , the investigations are not conclusive .
According to the Canadian Cancer Society , studies on Vitamin E are inconsistent .
While a study found a reduction in the risk of prostate cancer , another one showed an increase .
Vitamin D ’ s effect on cancer has not yet been clearly demonstrated .
Furthermore , Mr Beaulieu stresses how important it is to talk to his doctor about his concerns and his family preoccupation .
&quot; The implementation of a test test does not lead to cancer . &quot;
The Higgs-Boson
The announcement of the most likely discovery of Higgs-Bosons last summer has a certain upshot , and this is good reason .
It is true that this body is not a factor in the mechanism that is responsible for the mass of all objects in the universe .
Finally , this is the last particularity , which is the result of the standard model - our best or &quot; least incorrect &quot; statement of the nature and behaviour of the subject - but it has not been observed empiredly .
But for physicists , it is not yet fully certain that this is the Higgs .
We know without the shadow of a doubt that we have a real new particle and that it is very similar to the Higgs-Boson model .
Moreover , this seems to be confirmed by new data presented this week at a major physic-congress in Kyoto , but there are still data to be fully sure of .
But we still assume that it is about Higgs , because there seems to be a little risk of decepting ourselves and looking at what is going on .
There is an inevitable law in this world , which means that two objects cannot be available at the same place .
It is not possible to violate this rule - and try not to be too strong because you are going to wash .
For even if the particularity is a really strange , the Pauli &apos; s own prohibition is that , in fact , two particles , that are not the same space , can occupy the same space at the same time when they are in the same &quot; quantum state &quot; , which is a &quot; state &quot; , and that is the most common .
The physicists share the particles in two categories on this basis
In one corner are the good citizens who are called Fermione and who are eating the Pauli-principle .
And in the other , the bosons , a bit of anarchists , which are not sacred , certainly do not this principle , which means that they can in fact be able to find in the same place at the same time .
The group of the Berkeley Laboratories , which are in fact absolutely astonished by the Berkeley Laboratories , are on the list : the mesons that we are not treating here and the &quot; power particles &quot; , which are spreading the great powers of the nature and which are somehow associated with the Higgs-Boson .
However , it must be stressed here that these bosones are not all such exotic creatures as you might think .
If you are able to read this chronicle , then only thanks to a Bosons of exceptional banality : the photon or the &quot; light particle &quot; that is the &quot; Bote &quot; of electromagnetic strength .
If a particle is accelerated or the direction is changed , the electromagnetic field is &quot; interrupted &quot; in this place , in such a way as a pond stone that has been thrown into a pond .
This &quot; disturbing &quot; creates an electromagnetic wave ( light , infrared or ultrasviolet radiation , etc . ) , and this wave is nothing more than a photon and thus one of the bosones &quot; carrier of power &quot; .
Stite Area
The same applies to Higgs-Boson , with the difference that another field , the Higgs field , must be &quot; interrupt &quot; to show this boson .
However , the higgs field is much more stable than the electromagnetic field ; the reactor has to achieve very high energy , a bit comparable with a frozen pond , whose surface could be distrustful only by a very large rock .
This is why a huge number of particles such as CERN are required - the Large Hadron Collider is a ring with a size of 27 km - to achieve such energies .
The analogy with the electromagnetic field is once again helpful to explain the relationship between the Higgs and the mass .
In fact , they are not all particles and not all the materials interacting with electromagnetic field .
Some , such as magnets , do so , but others , for example , would not keep a sheet of paper on the fridge
And equally interacting not interact with the Higgs field : those who do , possess a mass , while the others ( as the photo itself ) do not have a mass .
For what these research can be &quot; good &quot; , ask Mrs Plamondon ?
For science , they are the testing of the standard model ( SM ) and they also allow physicians to thoroughly examine any deviations between the observations and predictions of the SM .
There are , moreover , many physicists who hope that such deviations will be found , because the slightest difference is to open a door to a new physics and to plug some holes of the model .
It has to be said that the latter is still very flawless , because there is no explanation for gravity ( ups ! ) and dark matter , which provides about 80 % of the universe &apos;s dimensions ( again ! ) .
However , such deviations have not been found to date at CERN

The effects of these research on the general population are more difficult to predict , but it would be wrong to assume that there are no
