With Bitcoin , Payment and Buy without Bank
The opposite of the current monetary exchange on the basis of central banks , identified transactions and administrative charges between the parties involved .
Moreover , as often in these technologies , a political vision is tangible : the conviction that the current monetary system , designed by banking monopolies , leads to financial crises .
In fact , the Bitpit created by Satoshi Nakamoto ( a Pseudonym ) is both a virtual currency ( in dollars , Euro , etc . ) and a protocol for secure exchange such as BitTorrent , which allows direct exchange of files .
15,000 computers in the network already account for about 200,000 transactions .
Some thousand websites accept bitcoins as donations or as payment funds .
After the match of Bitcoin reached a maximum of 30 dollars ( 23 euros ) , he fell to 2 dollars a month later , to 2 dollars before he recovered to around 10 dollars ( the courses are listed on the Bitcoincharts.com website ) .
Nothing particularly different from the world of world trade in real currencies or financial products .
Yet the European Central Bank ( ECB ) has shown interest in a report on virtual currencies published in October .
She describes Bitcoin as &quot; the virtual currency with the greatest success &quot; , &quot; in competition with the dollar or euro &quot; and &quot; similar to traditional currencies &quot; .
Bitcoin is different from other types of virtual currencies such as &quot; Credits &quot; , which are used to make progress in a video game that you can win or buy ( and sometimes exchange ) .
The social network Facebook has also developed such a system .
However , every time the trade is monitored and processed by a central authority
With Bitcoin , all network nodes simultaneously cover the invoices of the invoice , auditors , money issuers , and buyers and vendors
How does this network work ?
Each transaction between two users is actually taking place between two email addresses in the form of an email
With the difference that the user can choose another address for each payment , which ensures anonymity .
A number of data related to this transaction is signed electronically by a double encryption system .
This way the network can check the authenticity of the transaction .
The content of the file is also possible to ensure that the traged bitcoins are available in the public accounts of the public accounts widely used throughout the network .
The decisive step is to add this new transaction to this book .
This is done on a mathematical task that is started on computers , with the winner who is a kind of premeditate central banker who has the privilege to add this extra line .
This is a mess of the file , i.e. the conversion of a large file into a shorter and clear electronic fingerprint .
The computer &quot; take &quot; the new transaction and add a number before the whole &quot; chicken &quot; .
The goal is to find the number that gives a special fingerprint ( many nulls at the beginning ) .
If this number is found , the other knots can check for the correct .
The transaction is therefore permanently linked to the chain of all other transactions and any modification would change fingerprinting .
If a user is to pay a very fast ( less than 10 minutes ) to the same money , only one of the two transactions will be validated by the network and the other will remain without interlinking , as both have different fingerprints .
The computer that has solved the task has 50 bitcoins .
To prevent inflation , this reward is regularly halved , probably before the end of 2012 .
The Bitcoins are thus limited to 21 million but are still part of a 100 millionstel , which leaves a certain amount of space to be used ...
In addition , the difficulty of the task is increased with every improvement in computing power
The life of the network has already had ups and downs .
The web pages that provide the services for bitcoins were attacked and the Bitcoin deposits stolen .
&quot; The weak point does not concern the actual protocol &quot; , Pierre Noizat , who has just introduced Payment , has introduced a company for payment with real money and uses Bitcoin &apos;s network .
The ECB also reports about the possibilities of money laundering using this anonymous service .
However , cash also has these shortcomings .
Important actors such as Wikipedia refuse donations of this kind
Other people such as the blog blog WordPress will accept them .
Recently Adi Shamir and Dorit Ron , the Weizmann Institute in Israel , analyzed the accounting book and showed that almost 80 % of the bitcoins are not in circulation .
A &quot; Mega-Finder &quot; started in November .
&quot; Thirty thousand dollars were exchanged &quot; , Jon Holmquist is working for the Coinabul company , which converts Bitcoins into gold .
Pierre Noizat , who is also a writer of a book about this currency , firmly believes in the potential of this technology as a transaction network
Its system Paytunia is equivalent to a credit card ( with real money ) or a non-contact payment with a mobile phone , but Bitcoin uses the validation of transactions that are cheaper .
The owner is also managing his identity and can remain anonymous .
The system can be easily implemented with traders , and the latter must not install new terminals or computer programs .
You just need to give a address that can be &quot; photographed and recognized &quot; by a phone , Pierre Noizat will assure you that he has thousands of users .
It is a general trend , which revisions the hierarchical systems in favour of more horizontal systems .
&quot; It will take some time to get bitch but , in 2013 , a turning point is forecast .
The ECB , in its report , is in fact proposing to reassess the various risks to a successful currency in the event of a success of this currency
