In Israel , Ukrainian tourists expect sacred sites , the nails of the world and a sea of Sole .
The land of Gelobland combines the glory of biblical truths , modern comfort and an untouched nature .
AIF gives you the five most important reasons for visiting Israel .
Forests in the Holy Sites
Visit the River Jordan , where Jesus was baptized .
It means that all who are swimming in this river receive God ’ s blessing .
Galiläa is the place where Jesus has made his miracle : the transformation of water to wine on a wedding , walking on the water , the depression of the lake and fishing .
Jesus was also a great man of the Great Testament .
Most of the holy , however , are found in Jerusalem
The king of Jesus Christ , and the Cross of Jesus Christ , make this a journey .
The path begins at the Roman fortress Antonia , Pretorium , where the court was , and through the streets of the Old Town , it was the tomb of Golgotha , where the Cross , the Salation stone and the tomb of Jesus are located .
Here , a Christian view of the world is being formed , symbolizing the savoury of humanity .
The Holy Cross of Jerusalem is on the spot where a Christian legend grew to grow the tree from which the Cross was made for the Cross of Jesus .
In Jerusalem is also the most sacred place of the Jewelry - the Caverns , the remains of a temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 AD .
Traditionally , people are leaving people with different beliefs of faith , who will then be fulfilled .
A Journey
The ruins of the fortress Massada form the remains of secret forests against enemies , which built the Great of Great in 25 AD for his family .
They are on a rock wall in the mountains 450 meters above sea level .
Only mountain climbers can reach the ruins by their own strength .
All others are leading a glimpse of this historic summit .
In the north of the country in 1600 to 2040 metres , the famous ski resort Hermon is attracting countless tourists in the winter months .
The river is also accessible by a shuttle bus .
The ski slopes have a total length of 45 kilometres .
According to a legend , there were allegedly pagan gods at the mountain summit
Unique Museums
There are almost 300 museums in this country .
All of them are not possible to visit .
But at least the five most interesting of them should be allowed to visit .
This is the most important area of the island .
There are ancient Qumranros or Scrolls of the Death Sea found in Felshöhlen in the Judaetian desert , and some 500 thousand archaeological and anthropological exhibits are being found .
The Museum of Art in Tel Aviv is also worth visiting .
There is the collection of works of Impressionists and Expressionists Monet , Pissaro , Renoir , Cézanne , Sisley , Matisse , Modigliani , Chagall and Picasso .
In Akko you can visit the Museum in Bad Al Basha , which has several halls of ancient Turkish baths , with sculptures by the then visitors and bathing establishments .
In Caesarea you should visit the unique private Ralli Museum , where you can admire sculptures by Dali and Rodin .
There is neither a museum guide nor souvenir shops .
The admission is free , and donations are not accepted .
The fifth museum , the Holocaust Museum and Yad Vashem in Tel Aviv , is one of the most dramatic chapters of history .
The most important department is the monument for children , which was built to commemorate the 1.5 million children who were destroyed in concentration camps and chambers of gas .
When entering the room there is total darkness .
Stars radiate .
And they are the names of the Jewish children and the countries in which they died .
Ukraine is also mentioned there .
A Health
The three most important recreational areas of Israel are on the shores of the Mediterranean , Red Sea and the dead Sea .
There are swimming pools , water parks , dolphin and ocariums on each of the three places .
Amaadly , the Red Sea is also being damaged in the winter months , as water temperatures are not below 21 ° C and air is warming to 23 ° C.
The dead sea is even more heated and it is all well below the year .
This unusual sea , with a surface of 417 metres below sea level , is the most deepest sea in the world .
Its turquoise waters have a high salt content and thus even un-boilers are easily on the surface
The surrounding landscape is indescribable .
Visitors come here to treat the skin ( natural salt and healing sludge ) , and to treat skin inflammation , allergies , asthma , eczema , arthritis , bronchitis , strain and to relieve strain nerves .
The Secrets of the Age
The city is also home to the old town of Tel Aviv , the city of Jaffa on the Mediterranean
This city was dominated by the famous sea path , Egypt , Syria , Anatolia and Mesopotamia .
The city is mentioned in ancient Greek and Egyptian legends .
According to the legend , Noah built his arche here , and Perseus saved the beautiful Andromeda , which he had a long and happy life in this place .
Visitors are happy to climb through the narrow streets named after star characters .
The legend is to be the legend after all the races that touch the walls of the cup with their star characters .
In Jaffa you can recomend newcomers from all over Israel and even other countries in photo sequences .
In Caesarea , the city of King Herodes , you can stroll through the Roman theater and conquer the fortress of the Crusades .
In Roman times Caesarea was the most important city of Judoba and residence of Roman statesman , including Pontius Pilatus .
The theatre is currently being renovated and is currently being redecorated .
Tourist List
