In the United States Fast-Foods and Supermarket workers
Every fourth American youth is eventually sitting behind the Kasse of Mc Donald &apos;s
In the last few days , there has been massive protests in the US against low wages in shops of Walmart and restaurants of popular fast-food chains such as Mc Donald &apos;s , Burger King , Taco Bell , Wendy &apos;s and Kentucky Fried Chicken .
Nobody can predict whether the protests will be even more outrageous , or whether they will soon be coming to the air
The protests are supported by trade unions and several leftist non-profit organisations
In addition to increasing modest wages by simple walmtypes and fast-food workers , the organizers of the protests are pursuing the goal of establishing trade unions .
This industry is hardly a trade union .
46 Cents per year ?
The protests started last week after Thanksgiving , on the so-called Black Friday , where sales in the US were taking place , which attracted millions of customers , which sometimes led to handcrafts .
On this day , some Walmartstaff , from which there are 2 million , are left to work , and they are insulting and denying their work together with trade unions and left-wing , left-wing groups of the chain , whose target groups are
Walmart sells all products , from windmills to hunting and battery batteries to dust and milk .
The raw material in the Walmart bottles is between 8 and 27 % cheaper than in large supermarkets .
This is why many of the small-scale WalMola workers are only buying their own jobs .
The prices and the range of goods made Walmart one of the largest companies in the USA .
Critics , according to the experts , can often sell the goods to Walmart , because the employees are badly paid
The latter also cover difficult working conditions , such as missing forklifts or handlers .
The participants of the &quot; Black Friday &quot; protests were asking for wage increases and reported that the contribution to the company &apos;s health insurance was $ 30 a month .
A typical Walmartworker , which deserves 9.5 USD a day , could not afford this increase , they said .
Scientists from California University of Berkeley show that if the company increases the average wage to 12 dollars , Walmart would cost $ 3.2 billion .
That is about 1.1 % more than it is now donating pay .
If Walmart had completely to pay the salvage to the customer , every purchase would cost only 46 cents more in future .
For them , it would be more than 12.39 dollars compared to today ’ s total .
The general public of Walmart , who is a member of the German Federal Republic of Germany , is satisfied that it only has a test of protests
The Black Friday took place in its shop from 8 a.m. to midnight on Thursday until midnight , and during this period Walmart sold about 5 000 articles per second .
The Walmart boxes on the Black Friday ran almost 100 million transactions .
The spokesperson of the company , Dan Fogelman , who , in an interview , called Huffington Post , claimed that a total of less than five &quot; Walmartworkers workers , and the protest campaign only &quot; another PR trick &quot; organized by the protests was the only thing that the protest was about .
&quot; Free Kasse ! &quot;
The protests went on this week in New York , where their goal was not to make Walmart-Lions ( who are not in a much desired city and thus to date ) , but McDonald &apos;s and other low-cost restaurants .
McDonald &apos;s says that the company sold billions of portions , but you don &apos;t give you a disease and you are not paid for your honest work !
Jumaane Williams , member of New York City Council
At present , the minimum wage is the hour after federal and New York legislation at 7.25 dollars .
In Fast-Food-restaurants , the minimum wage is raised , but not too strong , and on average their simple staff in New York will receive USD 8.90 .
Less than she deserves no one in this expensive city .
How it is possible to spend money in New York is not incomprehensible to me .
