Few saw it as the main source of income or planned to stay longer there .
Now , when I talk to colleagues from McDonald &apos;s , people are constantly being asked to pay their wages to them and sometimes even to feed their children .
On the other hand , in the Forum Wall Street Journal , the author of the newspaper notes that it is irresponsible to get children , if you do not know how to eat them .
The protests that took place on Thursday at 6.30 a.m. in front of the McDonald &apos;s , in the Duke Street and in Madison Avenue , demanded that the cleric and kitchens of Fast-Food-restaurants would receive a minimum wage of $ 15 a day , which is more than doubling the current minimum wage .
