- not necessarily , but this is a mutual convergence .
I think that in the next few years we must , above all , work on developing new sensor types which will enable people to be more closely involved .
This can be the laser sensor , for example , because it provides a good resolution in depth , which is very important .
- What are the requirements of your work with the Xbox cinematic sensors on modern cameras ?
Does it mean a resolution , depth or anything else ?
- The current generation is basically a good starting point for our work in the field of three-dimensional detection .
Of course , 8 Megapixels would not be bad with a speed of 1000 fps
But the main thing is not the megapixel itself but the quality of matrix and depth .
All the current technologies are not good enough for us , because the developers of the algorithms have more work .
Not only the resolution along the X- and Y- but also along the Z-axis must be taken into account .
The speed and the number of images per second are also important .
The movements of people are extremely dynamic and frankly , the 30 fps are too little for gestures .
Stephen Betishes developed a touch sensor in our laboratory in Redmond with a regulatory delay of between 1 to 100 milliseconds , with today &apos;s commercial sensors being closer to the second value ( 60 to 100 ) .
Not everyone understands how much interaction between man and machine influences .
I just needed a manual for my work , just without touch control and with more pictures per second .
- Can the number of cameras not be increased ?
- Kinum currently works with three &quot; cameras &quot; , one of which is an infrared transmitter and the second one is a receiver for the reflected signal
And the third camera is actually a normal RGB camera .
It does not serve to calculate object depth .
More cameras could solve the problem ...
Or the problem is more important , as more calculations are needed
It would be a flexible , kinect-like system where we could play with different camera assumptions to determine how we help to determine a position in three dimensional ways .
- If I remember , Microsoft did not present its glasses to Google , unlike Google .
Do you not think that , with the use of the advanced technology of the extended reality , glasses have the best prospects ?
- Of course , it is not easy to keep a smarter on the handphone , but I think the most beautiful is a &quot; changing &quot; reality , which we could turn out to be a cloud on the smartphone , which is a great option to use .
The Brille is a personal gadget and it is your strength ( private only you can see ) but also its weakness , because an expanded reality by glasses prevents you from working with others on virtual objects .
- We are currently faced with the fact that the manipulation of virtual holographic in the air is not only a Tony Stark from Iron Man , but also a Normalmormorist .
There is a problem , often the criticism of this idea : there is no emptiness reaction !
The hands are not really feeling anything !
What answers do your group want to give to this objection
- I often talk about the fact that the enlarged reality is the seventh breakthrough in interaction between humans and machine .
I think the eighth breakthrough could well be the integration of tactical perception .
An interesting method is currently using the second hand as a rather unusual projection .
She is taking the pressure out !
There are , however , also technologies that are geared towards the &quot; images in the air &quot; , which are actually being used to give the interval of some sophisticated ultrasonic rays on a certain point where the finger is , a feeling that is still so weak , that someone has to be asked about the handles .
There are also bands for the handgrip that are able to influence the nerves in the fingers , which is a potential direction .
- Have you tried to overlist the brain ?
It is to be remembered that it feels what it should feel when it comes to something ?
- This is a good idea , so we have not tried it .
Here is a more than a thing that we are going to fight for a long time , namely a person who is physically in a closed space , he is looking for instead in an open , practically infinite space ; here we are working on concepts with trawlers ( others as in fitness studios ) , mobile platforms and large balls .
