Poland and space .
Last week , Poland was the European Council of Ministers of the European Space Agency , ESA , which was the second member of this space authority , and it is thus the second member country from the former eastern bloc ( after the Czech Republic , which became ESA member of the European Union on
In 1994 , Poland started close cooperation with ESA and involved several ESA projects in the following years .
Poland ’ s path to space , however , started to happen much earlier
Polish cosmosmians were also involved before World War II , and they did not always understand the understanding of this .
I recall , for example , the speech by A. Šternfeld , on 6 December 1933 , in the Warsaw Observatory , where the author presented the idea of &quot; entrance to Kosmonautik &quot; .
The ideas of the young engineer ( born 1905 ) , however , were cold and after years , Šternfeld reminded himself that only Dr Jan Gadomski had shown his work .
In 1934 , the &quot; entrance to Kosmonautik &quot; won the Prix REP Hirsch , which Robert Esnault-Pelterie and André Louis Hirsch raised .
Dr. Jan Gadomski ( born 1899 - 1966 ) was an important proponent of astronomy and space .
In Polish magazines he published hundreds of articles and wrote several books on these scientific disciplines .
Gadomski &apos;s worldwide contribution to development of space travel was partly appreciated by the fact that one of the craters was named after him on the moon &apos;s erased side .
In 1925 , a railway tanker was built in Poland , which was planned to carry a missile drive .
Unfortunately , the author of the draft and the details of this project remained unaware .
It has not even been clarified whether the rocket should be used to launch or brake the dragon .
The information is only available from the contemporary press .
In 1933 , the Polish infantry began to deal with rainy events .
The research carried out the Institute Komórka Techniki Uzbrojenia in cooperation with Prof. Mieczyslaw Wolfke and Prof. Gustaw Mokrzyckiegi .
The documents provided clearly show that research was a step forward in practical tests .
The research was then interrupted by the invasion of Germany &apos;s Wehrmacht .
In 1937 , the technical press of the company , which was created in the year 1937 , was published in the &quot; Rakieta &quot; plant , and the plant &quot; Rakieta - torpeda powietrzna i rakietobomba lotnicza &quot; of the author Leliwa-Krzywoblocky .
