The Worlest World ’ s Worlest : Human Working Cases of Kawah Ijen
For four euros , the Indonesian volcano agents are putting their lives and their health at risk when they carry 70 kilo sulfur over the steep , deep paths .
There are people for whom their work is hell , and others work in the hell .
This is the case of Anto Wijaya , one of the 400 mind-workers who earn their lives by getting sulphur from the volcano Kawah Ijen in the east of the Indonesian island of Java .
To do this , he must go down to the land of his kraters every day , where the sulphur sulphate gas is emitted into contact with the air .
After breaking large sulphur stones , which could be weighed up to 70 kilo , he transported them to two bamboo basins on his shoulder on the shutdown paths of stone .
It is only 250 metres to the tip of the volcano , which is a height of 2386 metres , but the erected carrier needs more than 40 minutes to climb the turtles , and to keep the balance and to take care of them , so that they do not slip and fall .
They know that every step can be taken to a French tour , which has been a triumph of the Kawah Ijen years ago .
Kawah Ijen minenworkers earn 5 eurocent for each kilo of sulfur they reduce .
On the other hand , they are moving to the streets of the tourist , which they are photographing like circus and run with the tired heavy basins three kilometres to the guard , which a minencompany has a little further below 1850 metres .
The company is PT Candi Ngrimbi , which has since 1960 used the ancestors of the volcano and ( never better ) to exploit its workers , which they paid 662 Indonesian rupia ( 5 euro ) for each kilo of sulfur .
It is then sold to the oil rowers ( 83 Eurocent ) , because this mineral is widely used in everyday life , and is used to produce strawberries , fireworks , fireworks , and even to the shelves of sugar .
&quot; We are usually 70 kg , we get about 46,000 rupies ( 3.8 euros ) , and Anto explains that it is usually three routes a day .
For each track he takes three hours , he has completely succeeded , but at the end of the day he has together 138,000 rupia ( 11,5 euros ) .
What is a malicious reward for such a schizophrenic effort , but is threw three times what he would earn with the field of work .
