After the Court of Appeal of the United States , which has confirmed the reformation of the liabilities of Vitro , which has been achieved through a trade agreement in Mexico , it is not a disastrous precedent for each national company with subsidiaries in the neighbouring country , which have problems in payment .
So it could be said that the procedures for the survival of companies that permit Mexican legislation are not valid in the countries of stars and Stripes in contravention of international agreements .
In practice , the judgment of the judge of the judge , Harlin Hale , in Bancarrotas in the Northern District of Texas on 15 June , has made it possible for Mexican companies to be subject to the seizure of their property beyond the Bravo River .
However , the decision opens the largest glass producer in Mexico to call the Supreme Court of the United States for three inconsistencies .
While the judge points out that creditors must be subject to the United States ’ right to bankruptcy , the Fifth Circuit ’ s appeal to the World Bank is the first to be the main trading process in Mexico .
The first point would be that international cooperation in cases of payment insolvency in the case of non-bank companies is not known .
In fact , the United Nations model for the unification of international trade law was created for this purpose , with the American Law Institute being used as a sleeve .
Secondly , the judgment that , without the votes of the companies , after recognising the liabilities of the bankruptcy of Vitro , the branches of Vitro , the majority of companies would not have been able to achieve the necessary majority for restructuring .
However , this possibility is recognised by Mexican laws .
Vitro is not the first to allow this scheme to be approved .
There are a half-dozen examples , including agreements mex and Comercial Mexicana , whose liabilities are confirmed by the Group of the Instituto Federal de Concursos Mercantiles ( Federal Institute for Trade Accountability ) .
It is also true that , after moving the votes of the parties to Vitro , the creditors of the banks , who were opposed to Vitro , the victors , such as the Geier Fund , Aurelios Capital , Aurelios Convergencia , Elliot Internacional and Liverpool Limited , would have achieved a majority .
The vote would be 45 % against 37 % .
This is not taken into account by the Court
On the other hand , Vitro is responsible for its difficult situation since 2008 in the context of the great economic crisis in the United States , which gave to the country
For this reason , the González Sada family is opposed to the same appeal court , so that the vote in plenary is held , that is to say all the judges , because only three of them voted
If the case is not granted , the Cerciorn objection to the trial is called for by a higher authority , in this case by the Supreme Court of the United States .
The main concern is that the Court of Justice has sent a document to the government of Mexico , which was set up by the government of the Italian Government , which was described by Vitro , which was described in the Legal Trade Agreement , and which it has to say , that it has strictly complied with the agreements signed by both countries in order to comply with Chapter 15 of the United States &apos; bankruptcy law .
It also states that the country has the principles of the United Nations Commission for international trade , that is to say the rules on the cases of cross-border insolvency , which guarantee equality between debtors and creditors .
