Héctor &apos; Hetin &apos; Reyes : &apos; Basketball was my life &apos;
The world champion of basketball , Héctor &quot; Hetin &quot; Reyes , was a corbsport for more than 60 years and has traveled to the whole world .
Few of Puerto Rico have such a great intellectual collection of the history of the country &apos;s basketball , such as Héctor &apos; Hetin &apos; Reyes
Before joining the wheelchair in 2008 , he was part of this sport , when he was a player of lower classes , players of the first national league , a sponsor and director in BSN with the Vaqueros de Bayamón , or the president of the basketball band .
&quot; I was on the back of a while , when I was on the basketball , even several , the head of the team , who was the first to be the national team of the national team , and I remembered Reyes when visiting Primera Hora , where he was home to him at Bayamón , where he lives with Isabel , his true wife , who lived for more than 50 years .
&quot; Basketball was my life . &quot;
Reyes does not exaggerate this statement .
The walls of his house are almost all decorated with photos and memories of his long career and are testimony to them
Bayamón in the Heart
The most emotional memories are those who , in his time , remember the Vaqueros from the middle of the 50s as a player until 1982 , where he celebrated his 15-year anniversary as a co-manager or manager of the club .
&quot; I have been my best years , I enjoyed most , because I was part of eight masterpieces of the Vaqueros since 1967 as the managing director , co-manager and coach .
They were many enduring years , including the five championships from 1971 to 1975 .
And then I passed with a championship in 1981 , the year of the debut of Jerome Mincy at BSN .
From then on &quot; Cuco &quot; took over , which was a very good administrator , says Reyes .
