Who was the best player of Puerto Rico ?
That was without doubt Piculín Ortiz .
Its figures at the level of international tournaments are impressive .
No one in Puerto Rico has dominated such a level as Piculín .
And this without taking into account the various leagues in which he played .
Who was the best coach from Puerto Rico ?
This is a difficult issue .
We had a number of good trainers such as Julio Toro , Flor Meléndez , Carlos Morales , Raymond Dalmau , Armandito Torres
From the boys , I like the work of Leo Arill .
What do you think the best thing you &apos;ve achieved in the association ?
I was part of the most successful era of the national team from 1988 to 1995 , which allowed BSN to be up to 17 teams in a season in the 1990s .
What remains to be done ?
There are things I have introduced , such as regionalisation of the lower categories .
The guys in Ponce , for example , play in their area , and only in the national playoffs to meet teams from other corners of the island .
Today , children are making unnecessary travel and games .
At least I see the result of the compulsory training and courses for trainer , Tango official and arbitrator .
I am proud of this .
What do you do today ?
I listen to music , watch videos of my time in YouTube , enjoy my grandchildren and go and go to a basketball game .
And , of course , I enjoy the society of my wife Isabel , who has always been my site
